cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.PE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing a wireless access network using the LoRa protocol. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the transmission rates and interference treatment of LoRa. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a possibility as the paper models the behavior of multiple LoRa nodes transmitting packets. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper analyzes the performance of LoRa networks and proposes tuning to improve performance. 
- cs.PE (Performance) is a possibility as the paper studies the scaling of packet reception probabilities as a function of node density and transmission rate.
